Background
Degrees of Freedom (DOF): Defines the independent movements a robotic system
can perform.
2-DOF Manipulator: Typically enables two motions, such as rotation.
Applications: Suitable for simplified tasks like pick-and-place or planar movement.
Human Motion Mapping: Uses gesture recognition and devices like motors or
cameras.
Motion Translation: Converts arm movements into robotic commands.
Challenges:
Latency: Disrupts real-time interaction.
Precision: Needed to avoid errors.
Importance: Accurate Human-Robot Interfaces (HRI) are critical for effectiveness.
Applications in Real Life
Medical Applications
Rehabilitation devices and physical therapy robotics
Prosthetics control for individuals with disabilities
Industrial Applications
Precision tasks in assembly and inspection
Remote operation in hazardous environments
Educational and Research Applications
Training tools for robotics education
Consumer Applications
Gaming and virtual reality systems
Smart home applications
Methodology : Computer Vision
Computer Vision is a field of computer science which
enables computers to interpret and process visual
data from the world
Main Field Covered:
Image acquisition and processing.
Object detection,tracking and image generation.
Feature extraction and geometric computations.
In robotics : path planning, object recognition, HRI,
obstacle avoidance, mapping, inspection and quality
control etc.
Fig: Object pick and placed
based on the annotation from
the images
Image Mapping and Coordinate system
Image Representation: Images are represented as 2D arrays of pixels.
Coordinate system: Origin (0,0) is usually at the top-left corner of the image.

What this all Means
Vision systems - Data that can be perceived in 2-d space.
As part of any NN optimization is key.
Sometimes optimization is subjective
Wrist movement was harder to track than elbow, does it need to be fixed?
If not the final output, data from the vision system must be communicated to
another device. (Wifi, Ethernet, BlueTooth)
Protocols and Requirements for communication
Decided on by what makes this data meaningful what are the priorities and goals.
This can be speed, this can be accuracy, etc.
At the end of the day finding the write combination of vision system, robot and
communication method is tricky because each will lead to a different result.
